{{Infobox journal | title = Marburg Journal of Religion | cover = Marburg Journal of Religion.jpg | editor = Edith Franke | discipline = [[Religious studies]] | language = Multilingual | abbreviation = | publisher = [[University of Marburg]] | country = [[Germany]] | frequency = Annual | history = 1996-present | openaccess = Yes | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://archiv.ub.uni-marburg.de/ep/0004 | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | RSS = | atom = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 44277913 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 1612-2941 | eISSN = }} The '''''Marburg Journal of Religion''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[electronic journal|online]] [[academic journal]] that publishes articles on empirical and theoretical studies of [[religion]]. The first issue having appeared in April 1996. The original concept was developed by [[Michael Pye]] together with his assistant Richard Böhme, who was the first Web Editor. The editorial team was broadened in 1999 to include Peter Antes ([[Hanover|Hannover]]) and [[Andreas Grünschloß]] ([[Göttingen]]) and in 2007 Edith Franke ([[Marburg]]). Doreen Christen became Web Editor in 2002. The first separate Reviews Editor was Monika Schrimpf (from 2001) and this role was taken up by Katja Triplett from 2003.<ref>[http://archiv.ub.uni-marburg.de/ep/0004/about/editorialTeamBio/628]</ref>
Papers published in the ''Marburg Journal of Religion'' are documented and abstracted in the bibliographical journal ''[[Science of Religion (journal)|Science of Religion]]'', now published by [[Brill Publishers]] in [[Leiden]]. The abstracts published in the ''Marburg Journal of Religion'' itself may be published elsewhere on condition that full documentation of the article is provided.
